    <div class="pc_textlft">
        <h3>NEW TO VBA COMPETENCY-BASED TRAINING SYSTEM? </h3>
        <p>As a new user, the following sections of the website will provide you will the information that you will need to gain a better understanding of the process:</p>
        <ol>
            <li>Briefing Tools and Tips – Here you will find information that you can use to helps other understand the VBA Competency-based Training System. </li>
            <li>Project Status – This section contains information related to the current status of the VBA Competency-based Training System. </li>
            <li>Resources – Look in this section to find forms and other documents that can be used to request information and other resources that will help enhance your knowledge.</li>
            <li>Glossary – Unsure of a definition a term or phrase that you have heard used during briefings? Check here for competency related terms and definitions.</li>
            <li>FAQs – If you have questions, we have the answers in this section.</li>
            <li>Calendar – Check this section to get up-to-date information on upcoming testing dates and other Competency-based Training System events.</li>
        </ol>
  

 
 
 

        <h3>ARE YOU ALREADY FAMILIAR WITH THE VBA COMPETENCY-BASED TRAINING SYSTEM?</h3>
        <p>As an experienced user, there is information on the website that you can use to gain a more in-depth understand of the Competency-based Training System. Use the left-hand navigation to gain a more detailed understanding of the VBA Competency-based Training System.</p>
        <ol>
            <li>My Role Is – This section provided detailed information related to the roles and responsibilities of the Employee, Training Manager, First Line Supervisor, and Senior Management.</li>
            <li>Competency Model Reports by Service – If you want to know more about the competencies for your position, this is the section for you. </li>
            <li>Diagnostic Assessments by Service – As the CBTS expands, diagnostics assessments will be made available for additional positions. Click here to determine if there is a diagnostic assessment available for your Service/position. You can also review this section to simply learn more about the structure and type of information used to create a diagnostic assessment. </li>
            <li>Badges – Badges or digital credentials allow you the opportunity to let others within the organization see your accomplishments. As you move through the CBTS, you will earn badges for a variety of accomplishments. Use this section to gain more information about badges and to see which badges are available for your Service/position and the requirements for each.  </li>
            <li>If you need a refresher, take a moment to review the slide shows and any of the information contained in the top navigation. </li>

        </ol>
    </div>

